4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING DIGITAL IDENTIFICATION LAWS; INCLUDING
5 DIGITAL VERSIONS OF LICENSES IN ALCOHOL, TOBACCO, AND MARIJUANA LAWS; AND AMENDING
6 SECTIONS 16-3-313, 16-11-305, AND 16-12-104, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 16-3-313, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "16-3-313. Periodic government or tribal-issued identification data destruction. (1) A business
12 that scans a person's physical or digital version of a person's government or tribal-issued identification to
13 determine the person's age solely for the sale of age-restricted items:
14 (a) shall use data or metadata from the scan only to determine the person's age;
15 (b) may not transfer or sell that data or metadata to another party; and
16 (c) shall permanently delete any data or metadata from the scan within 180 days.
17 (2) Nothing in this section may be construed to limit the collection and preservation of information
18 required by federal law for the sale of ephedrine or pseudoephedrine."
19
20 Section 2. Section 16-11-305, MCA, is amended to read:
21 "16-11-305. Sale or distribution of tobacco products, alternative nicotine products, or vapor
22 products to persons under 18 years of age prohibited. (1) A person may not sell or distribute a tobacco
23 product, alternative nicotine product, or vapor product to an individual under 18 years of age, whether over the
24 counter, by vending machine, or otherwise.
25 (2) If there is a reasonable doubt as to the individual's age, the seller shall require presentation of
26 a physical or digital version of a driver's license or other generally accepted identification that includes a picture
27 of the individual.
28 (3) If the seller scans a physical or digital version of a person's government or tribal-issued
